      <strong>What is Static GK?</strong> Static GK refers to fixed, non-changing facts about India — national symbols, constitutional provisions, geographical data, historical firsts. UPSC Prelims tests these directly as factual MCQs. Unlike current affairs, these facts don't change and can be memorised once.
