    <div class="gk-note">
      <strong>Exam strategy:</strong> UPSC Prelims tests static GK through direct factual questions and negative marking traps. Focus on what is <em>not</em> officially designated (e.g., no national sport, no official national language — Hindi is the official language of the Union under Article 343, not a "national language"). These distinctions are high-yield.
